          h3.head28
              | Responsive Columns <span class="head18 loose caps lite">(Varying Margin Widths)</span>
          p.text14
              | This responsive grid varies the gutter widths depending on the number of columns in your layout to enhance readability&period; Wider (fewer) columns are given more whitespace while narrow (more) columns receive a less generous portion&period;
          p.text14
              | The structure is pretty straight forward. To add 3 columns, just give 3 divs <span class="callout"><code>class="col-1of3"</code></span>â€”adding <span class="callout"><code>class="col-1of3 last"</code></span> to the final div to remove the right margin. There aren't any pushes or pulls. Just blocks to place content or leave blank <span class="callout"><code>class="col-1of3 blank"</code></span>. Example below.
      .hspace40
      .col-1of3
          .hereisacolumn.green.round4
              p.text12.center
                  code
                      &lt;div class&equals;&quot;col-1of3&quot;&gt;
      .col-1of3
          .hereisacolumn(style='background-color:transparent;')
              p.text12.center
                  code
                      &lt;div class&equals;&quot;col-1of3 blank&quot;&gt;
      .col-1of3.last
          .hereisacolumn.green.round4
              p.text12.center
                  code &lt;div class&equals;&quot;col-1of3 last&quot;&gt;
